pjv.evolution.genetic.algorithm

Class Individual

  • java.lang.Object
    • pjv.evolution.genetic.AbstractIndividual
      • pjv.evolution.genetic.algorithm.Individual
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<AbstractIndividual>

    public final class Individual
extends AbstractIndividual
    Class for individuals in evolutionary algorithm. It declares the genotype, among with related operations such as the mutation and the crossover, as well as computing fitness.

    • Method Detail

      • acceptanceProbability

        public double acceptanceProbability(double oldFitness,
                                    double newFitness,
                                    double temperature)
        The acceptance probability function takes in the old fitness, new fitness, and current temperature and spits out a number between 0 and 1, which is a sort of recommendation on whether or not to jump to the new solution.
        Parameters:
        oldFitness - fitness of the previous individual
        newFitness - fitness of the new individual
        temperature - declining temperature for simulated annealing
        Returns:
        probability of a new individual replacing the old one

      • repair

        public void repair()
        Make sure the solution is correct (that all the edges are covered) and if not, repair it. This function should be called every time we make a change to the genotype (mutate, crossover, init, etc.). If an edge is not covered, turn on the node with more edges.

      • mutate

        public void mutate(double mutationRate)
        Does random changes in the individual's genotype, taking mutation probability into account.
        Specified by:
        mutate in class AbstractIndividual
        Parameters:
        mutationRate - Probability of a bit being inverted, i.e. a node being added to/removed from the vertex cover.

      • crossover

        public Pair crossover(AbstractIndividual other)
        Crosses the current individual over with other individual given as a parameter, yielding a pair of offsprings. Algorithm will run 3-8 point crossover.
        Specified by:
        crossover in class AbstractIndividual
        Parameters:
        other - The other individual to be crossed over with
        Returns:
        A couple of offspring individuals

      • deepCopy

        public Individual deepCopy()
        When you are changing an individual (ie at crossover) you probably don't want to affect the old one (you don't want to destruct it). So you have to implement "deep copy" of this object.
        Specified by:
        deepCopy in class AbstractIndividual
        Returns:
